In a speech given on June 5, 2018, President Trump thanked the United States Marine Band and the United States Army Chorus for their performance. He emphasized the importance of standing for the National Anthem, stating that it is a way to honor the military, the country, and fallen heroes. The President expressed love for the country and its Constitution, and highlighted the current success of the United States, including record-low unemployment rates for various demographics and the growth of the economy. He concluded by emphasizing the unity and pride in being a part of America.